Have gained a few lbs on this bulk but not as much as I’ve wanted & that’s majorly due to me pulling back on eating when I shouldn’t because of body fat. But you can definitely keep your waist tight while on a bulk! Here are some tips I use to help keep that hip dysphoria from kicking in when I’m trying to grow 💪🏼🔑⬇️

1.) when you’re eating in a surplus, you want that metabolism firing on all cylinders! Activity level plays a huge role here & that hour a day in the gym isn’t enough activity if the rest of your day is sedentary. Shoot for those 10,000 steps!
2.) When your surplus is from mainly clean sourced foods, your body will respond SO MUCH BETTER! Stomach fat, energy levels, strength etc. So use that 80/20 rule & fuel that body properly with 80% Whole Foods 
3.) TRAIN THAT CORE! And not just bodyweight crunches but train core with progressive overload! Cable crunches, weighted decline crunches, weight OH sit ups are good examples! 
4.) Enjoy it! Think of this food as fuel & use it to your best ability by being intense & consistent with your training sessions. This accompanied with a 300-600 daily caloric surplus is the recipe for putting on weight 🔑 

You got this! Just remember you gotta eat big to grow!

Something that is never addressed by social media fitness “influencers” who are privileged is income inequality & how it can affect your health 

Not everyone can afford grass fed beef, organic chicken & fresh produce every week. And this clip shows you how that can take a major toll on your health 

So for those of you out there with a smaller food budget, I just wanted to remind you of some more cost effective items that can help you stay away from the cheaper processed junk they make SO affordable

Frozen chicken breast may not be as high quality but it’s cheaper & better than the processed, breaded stuff 👍🏼

Veggies from cans aren’t as quality either, but guess what? I would rather you have frozen chicken & canned peas than anything from McDonald’s 🔑 so just do the best your budget allows!

Carbs are thankfully always pretty cheap! Oats, rice, bread & pasta always have cheap brands! With bread just check that sugar & fiber content 🔑 

Chat with me below on how you feel about this, or if it has ever affected the way you grocery shop! Things have gotten pricy & it’s sadly a lot more expensive to be a healthy human nowadays

A common debate I hear is dumbbell vs barbell for chest day & there’s no one answer for EVERYONE here. Some people are able to bench their whole life without issues, but we all have different arm lengths & joint/ligament strength

Truth is dumbbell is king for targeted stimulus & has a less likely chance of joint injury. SO, that’s why it’s favorable compared to that fixed arm path you get with a barbell 

If you read an old school bodybuilding magazine it would say barbell bench is the king for chest growth & again they’re not wrong - it’s great! But again, the chest muscles wrap around close to our body & the arm path of a dumbbell allows us to get a greater stretch & leverage here 

So if you’ve been a fan of barbell, switch it up & try dumbbells for a bit! You may change sides 😈😂

I was always so scared of gaining any belly fat at the beginning of my fitness journey that I never ate enough (and still fight that mentality) 

You can definitely stay lean while still growing, the process is just slower & take more patience. But regardless when you do a proper bulk you WILL gain some body fat & that’s okay! Here are my tips for how I help keep waist semi in check while bulking ⬇️

You’re eating a lot more, so having a metabolism that is firing on all cylinders is important! 

🔑 20 min walks or 20 min of light cardio daily 
🔑 gallon of water a day & pink sea salt before every workout 
🔑 a surplus of high carbs/high protein but moderate fat (my body responds best this way)

Let’s talk about our weekly HRT injections 🚨 it’s common practice for doctors to tell you to administer your shot every 7-10 days (I’ve even heard ever 2 weeks). But this goes against so much common knowledge in the medical & bodybuilding field. 

You’ll see many athletes under the instruction of doctors taking their injection at smaller doses 2x per week or even a small dose daily. Why? Because the half life of testosterone cypionate crashes after a week & when you take your next shot, your levels spike again 

This spiking & crashing of hormones can lead to mood swings, energy loss, appetite irregularities, bad sleep & reduced recovery/muscle gain from your workouts. I’ve spoke with over 5 local doctors on this subject & all agree with me - get your labs done & try taking your shot every 3-5 days instead of every 7-10, you will feel much more stable in your hormone levels & I recommend chatting with your provider about it!

Even on a surplus, train core 2-3x a week & you’ll like how your strength in big lifts feel AND you’ll have a tighter mid section 

Core training is essential for not just aesthetics but function. Keep a strong AND functional core to protect you during heavy sets 🔑 

1st slide is a warm up before the other, more challenging movements. Get your lower back flat against the floor, hug those lower ribs against the floor & really engage those lower abdominals before raising your legs 

Then go into a set of these until you can’t do anymore. Rest 1 minute & repeat. 2 sets of this before other movements help my lower core feel more stable 

2nd slide are hanging toes to bar (which I had to work my way up to - start with knees to chest & then just raised legs to 90 degrees before trying these) 

3 sets of these shooting for 8-15 reps & pushing to failure each set 

3rd slide is an L sit hold & these are such a fun challenge in my opinion! I do 3 sets to failure & try to get at least 15 seconds on my last set & 30 on my first 

Last slide is decline weighted over head crunches & then I drop down to just bodyweight as I fail at those then hit failure again. Rest 90 seconds & repeat x 3

GO TRAIN THAT CORE! ❤️🤟🏼🔥

Rule of thumb here : it’s okay to eat potato chips & other guilty pleasures like it, BUT don’t get tricked into thinking you can consume huge amounts of a processed snack food & it be a “healthy food.”

I thought these chips were a great example of how marketing makes us feel like we’re making a healthier choice, when in reality there’s not much difference. 

Follow the 80/20 rule! You can still have chips, cookies, ice cream & the an alcoholic beverage without destroying your goals. 

Keep 80% of your day fueled with protein rich, nutrient dense meals & you can still enjoy those processed “treats” in moderation. You don’t have to give up things you enjoy, you just need to find a better balance that fits into your goals 

This is what I love helping people do! My meal plans have things like Oreo French toast, chocolate oatmeal protein balls, bacon cheese burgers, peanut butter shakes - you name it!  This life is short, we want to do things we enjoy. But why not do them in a way that allows us to get healthier, stronger & live longer? Instead of doing the polar opposite to that & sabotaging our health for little moments of pleasure 

There are 2 types of people - and we’re all capable of being both. Going into 2024, choose which one you want to be. Someone who creates discipline with their health which leads to FREEDOM, or will you continue to neglect it & make life harder down the road? Choice is yours 💪🏼❤️ and I’m here to provide you with 1:1 coaching help if you want me to show you how to begin! Message me to get started

I have a ton of clients & myself that are 4/20 friendly & I get asked the question often about staying on track when the munchies hit 

I just ate dinner & it was one of those nights I wanted to snack after. Sometimes I’ll indulge in a cookie or ice cream, but most of the time I like finding snacks that fit my macros better 

Try to keep mini sized sweets around so you can indulge within reason when you do & if there are things you have a weakness around - don’t buy a lot or any of that certain thing 

Popcorn with yeast is one of my savory favs & it might sound odd but you gotta try it! 

Some other things I & clients love are

Greek yogurt mixed with protein powder and/or fruit & honey 

Beef jerky sticks 

And Quest brand snack savory or sweet usually tastes 🔥

I LOVE oats with @dymatize protein mixed in (chocolate & PB is a fav) 

Yasso bars or halo top ice cream 

Rice cakes & low fat cream cheese 

Pretzels & hummus 

Kodiak cakes pancake mix 

Flavored tuna packs with crackers (I love the spicy flavors)

Home made milkshake with yogurt, ice & protein powder 

At the end of the day - you can have you sweets! But don’t let them wreck the hard work & goals you have. Learn that balance aspect & find things you enjoy to keep your cravings met MOST of the time that sensibly fit into your routine 💪🏼❤️

CORE WORK! Try to find enjoyment in it so you can create consistency because it pays off so much when you’re consistent with it! 

Core work isn’t talked about enough & it’s crucial to having great, injury free lifts, good posture & power/stability in your compound movements

Functional cores are important also! Aside from these movements I love hanging leg raises & kneeling cable crunhces. They provide a superior stretch on that eccentric portion that you don’t get with floor work - so try those as well! 

When I do even simple routines like this ^^^ I notice a difference in my core & my posture. If I slack on my core routines, I notice very quickly. So try these & see how you feel after a month of 2x per week!
